title.narrative: IR CHILD PROTECTION

description.narrative: WCARO provides high quality support to COs to strengthen practical, effective and efficient national child protection policies, systems, services and community mechanisms for prevention and protection from violence, abuse and exploitation and to prepare for and deliver humanitarian action - in collaboration with a wide range of child protection actors (including health, education, justice, governance, etc.), which contributes to Technical Excellence In Policy And Programmes. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Advocacy And Public Engagement, Developing And Leveraging Resources And Partnerships, Evaluations, Research And Data, Operational Support To Programme Delivery, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: UNICEF Country Office programmes and humanitarian action reflect national, regional and global priorities in line with corporate strategies and guidelines
